sentences: Nicholas John "Nic" Cester (born 6 July 1979) is an Australian musician, singer, songwriter and guitarist, known for being the frontman in rock band Jet alongside his younger brother Chris.
Jet's track "Are You Gonna Be My Girl", has won APRA Awards for 'Most Performed Australian Work Overseas' in 2006 and 2007.
Nicholas John Cester was born on 6 July 1979 and grew up in Melbourne.
The rock band, Jet, was initially formed in 1996 by Cester and Cameron Muncey while at High School.
